= Architecture =

== High-Level View ==
Pulse uses a classic layered architecture on .NET Framework 4.7.2.

=== Entry Points ===
* '''Pulse.Web'''
** ASP.NET MVC 5 UI layer
** OWIN cookie/forms-auth integration
** SignalR UI integrations
* '''Pulse.Api'''
** ASP.NET Web API 2
** OWIN JWT bearer auth
** service-first API endpoint layer

=== Core Layers ===
* '''Pulse.Core''': entities, contracts, interfaces
* '''Pulse.Infrastructure''': Oracle data access layer, repositories, event bus plumbing
* '''Pulse.Services''': domain services and business orchestration
* '''Pulse.ViewModels''' / '''Pulse.DataTransformationObjects''': transport models

== Dependency Injection ==
Autofac is used across web and API applications.
* API registration is broader and generally includes complete repository/service wiring.
* Web registration wires a narrower subset and integrates UI concerns (SignalR, page endpoints, auth flows).

== Data Access Pattern ==
* Oracle database access through Oracle Managed Data Access
* Query style via Dapper and Dapper.Oracle
* Repositories expose domain-centric reads/writes for services

== Application Domain Topology ==
The domain centers on roadmap-to-project execution:
* template catalogs: plants, categories, product hierarchy, roadmap templates, forms
* project instantiation: template snapshots copied into project-scoped structures
* execution: milestones, activities, tasks, forms, comments, attachments, notifications
* governance: access rights, module claims, user groups, AD integration

